               <msContents>
                  <summary>Letter from Egypt, written on papyrus. Alkeides writes to Nesiotes about Herodes, the tax collector, and what happened during Alkeides' absence. Possibly mentions the market place</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are at least 22.0 cm x 21.1 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">15 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers on the recto in the same hand as P.Duk.inv. 25; the address written along the fibers on the verso in large letters</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 2.5 cm.; lower margin of 2 cm.; left margin of 2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">Extracted from mummy cartonnage</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 24 was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 24</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>1 item : papyrus, four fragments of which three join, mounted in glass, right part is broken off</p>
